<subSubSection id="CA5E6A1ADF02BF2B788252A3EC6B579A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="D8DEDEC9BE3F1014D738325BCAA3F8C1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2FEB183FA6192B67C33F41A8CEE63E29" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species has been identified as 
<taxonomicName id="D2119D7DEAF9F10239660247CB5C9348" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mauritiana">
<emphasis id="4BC06399E4686BA86A0AFEB830E83CB9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea mauritiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is clearly related to that very variable species. However, it is immediately distinguished by the compound axillary inflorescences which reach 30 cm in length and are divided up to six times. Additionally, the sepals, corolla and capsules are all much smaller than in 
<taxonomicName id="C5BC3C547CAEAFA183D76FDF9005A83A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mauritiana">
<emphasis id="FD734492F46BBCE459FC6B7A9EAAEB62" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. mauritiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
